casebody.data:
Fourth Department,

February, 1938.

(February 11, 1938.) In the Matter of the Application of Steve Kaminsky, a Member of St. John’s Greek Catholic Church of Syracuse, New York, to Take Proof of Elections, etc., Pursuant to the Provisions of Section 25 of the General Corporation Law.

Motion for a stay pending appeal denied, without costs. The order appealed from was discretionary in character and we find no sufficient reason for staying its execution pending appeal. Present — Sears, P. J., Crosby, Taylor and Dowling, JJ.
